<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Wastewater Recycling Guide</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="recycle.css">
</head>
<body>
        <header><h1>Wastewater Recycling: Reuse and Benefits</h1></header>
    <div class="container">
        <section class="section">
            <h2>Treating Wastewater for Reuse</h2>
            <div class="treatment-options">
                <div class="treatment">
                    <img src="../images/recycle-images/sedimentation.JPG" alt="Primary Treatment">
                    <h3>Primary Treatment</h3>
                    <p>Removes large solids and particles through sedimentation.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="treatment">
                    <img src="../images/recycle-images/bio.jpg" alt="Secondary Treatment">
                    <h3>Secondary Treatment</h3>
                    <p>Uses biological processes to break down dissolved organic matter (e.g., activated sludge or biological filters).</p>
                </div>
                <div class="treatment">
                    <img src="../images/recycle-images/uv.jpeg" alt="Tertiary Treatment" style="height: 40%;">
                    <h3>Tertiary Treatment</h3>
                    <p>Further purifies water by removing nutrients like nitrogen and phosphorus, and may include advanced filtration, chemical treatments, or UV disinfection.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="treatment">
                    <img src="../images/recycle-images/osmosis.png" alt="Advanced Treatment">
                    <h3>Advanced Treatment</h3>
                    <p>Technologies like reverse osmosis, ultrafiltration, or advanced oxidation processes are used to treat water to a very high standard for potable (drinking) use.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <h2>Potential Uses of Recycled Wastewater</h2>
            <div class="uses">
                <div class="use">
                    <img src="../images/recycle-images/agriculture.jpg" alt="Agricultural Irrigation" style="height: 50%;">
                    <h3>Agricultural Irrigation</h3>
                    <p>Treated wastewater can safely be used to irrigate crops.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="use">
                    <img src="../images/recycle-images/cooling.jpg" alt="Industrial Use" style="height: 50%;">
                    <h3>Industrial Use</h3>
                    <p>Recycled wastewater can be used in industrial processes like cooling, washing, and manufacturing.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="use">
                    <img src="landscape.jpeg" alt="Landscape Irrigation">
                    <h3>Landscape Irrigation</h3>
                    <p>Used for maintaining public parks, golf courses, and private landscaping.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="use">
                    <img src="municipal.jpg" alt="Municipal Uses">
                    <h3>Municipal Uses</h3>
                    <p>Used for street cleaning, firefighting, and toilet flushing in public buildings.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="use">
                    <img src="../images/recycle-images/dust.webp" alt="Non-Potable Urban Use">
                    <h3>Non-Potable Urban Use</h3>
                    <p>Used in cooling systems, dust control, and non-potable urban needs.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="use">
                    <img src="../images/recycle-images/portable.JPG" alt="Potable Water Reuse">
                    <h3>Potable Water (Direct and Indirect Potable Reuse)</h3>
                    <p>Highly treated wastewater can be purified to meet drinking water standards and returned to the water supply.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <h2>Technological Methods for Wastewater Recycling</h2>
            <div class="technologies">
                <div class="technology">
                    <img src="../images/recycle-images/reverse osmo.png" alt="Reverse Osmosis">
                    <h3>Reverse Osmosis</h3>
                    <p>Removes even the smallest contaminants and pathogens from wastewater, making it safe for reuse.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="technology">
                    <img src="../images/recycle-images/wetlands.png" alt="Constructed Wetlands">
                    <h3>Constructed Wetlands</h3>
                    <p>Man-made systems that filter wastewater through plants and soil, mimicking natural wetlands.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="technology">
                    <img src="../images/recycle-images/activated-sludge-process.jpg" alt="Activated Sludge" style="height: 50%;">
                    <h3>Activated Sludge</h3>
                    <p>Biological processes used to break down organic materials and remove nutrients like nitrogen and phosphorus.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="technology">
                    <img src="../images/recycle-images/ozone.webp" alt="UV and Ozone Treatment">
                    <h3>UV and Ozone Treatment</h3>
                    <p>Disinfects water by using ultraviolet light or ozone, ensuring pathogens are removed.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <h2>Benefits of Wastewater Recycling in Minimizing Water Scarcity</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Conservation of Resources:</strong> Helps preserve natural water sources like rivers, lakes, and groundwater.</li>
                <li><strong>Decreased Environmental Impact:</strong> Reduces pollution and environmental harm from wastewater discharge.</li>
                <li><strong>Economic Savings:</strong> In many cases, using recycled water is more cost-effective than using fresh water.</li>
                <li><strong>Climate Resilience:</strong> Provides a reliable water source during periods of drought or water scarcity.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </div>
    
</body>
</html>
